      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">despierten wrote:</div><div class="orig">Red Robin, 16THM from Kashuan. <br /> <br />I constantly find myself NOT being able to save the party because I spend too much time dying.  I have yet to find a tank who knows how to hold aggro.  I am afraid to heal. . . <br /> <br />Thank you, <br /> <br />Red</div></div> <br /> <br />Yes it does depend on how good your party members are, I was privaleged to be playing with some pretty awesome players that knew their classes well and played as a team. As you get higher your tanks skills will increase and you should find yourself taking less and less hate. If you are fighting as a large (6+) group then you should not be getting much hate at all. Make sure you do not cast anything before the tank/mele have had time to actually hit the mob - taunting sometimes is not enough. Save your heals until the fight has started and don't heal out of fight unless absolutely necessary (you want to do this for SP reasons as well). When you high enough get yourself 'firm conviction' this can help damage mitigationa load and we think it is currently bugged so you get a wopping 80% dmg reduction as long as you have no buffs on you. This is way more than any tank. When fighting in a smaller party (Giant Crabs for example), you can pull hate very easily but you should be able to survive if you have the shield up, aegis boon, protect/shell, shock spikes etc. If you are fighting leves and getting hate then this is slightly different in my opinion. You tend to get more hate in these situations because eveyone is usually out for themselves to finish the leve or maximizing SP etc. I find that in these situations you need to fight only mobs that others are fighting and let them know clearly if you have agro. '/p [Help me out!] &lt;t&gt; [Taunt] [Please assist]!' is a macro you could use to let your tanks klnow you got hate and they need to get it off you. I have never had cause to use this because as I said my in-game buddies know what they are doing :)<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179">Loadstone Profile</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649">Thaumaturge Guide</a> <br /> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1229110.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
